# ===== SECURITY BEST PRACTICES =====
#
# 1. Pin exact versions (no ~= or >= operators)
#    Example: requests==2.31.0 (not requests>=2.0.0)
#
# 2. Use hashes to verify integrity (generate with pip-compile --generate-hashes)
#    Example: requests==2.31.0 \
#             --hash=sha256:abc123...
#
# 3. Audit dependencies before adding:
#    pip install pip-audit
#    pip-audit -r requirements.txt
#
# 4. Check package reputation:
#    pip show package-name
#    Visit PyPI page: https://pypi.org/project/package-name/
#
# 5. Review changelogs before updates
#
# 6. Use only-binary in pip.conf to prevent source builds

